'''Adam Lyth''' (born [[September 25]], [[1987]] in [[Whitby]], [[Yorkshire]], [[England]]) is a promising young cricketer who is contracted to play for [[Yorkshire County Cricket Club]] in the [[2007]] season.  He played regularly for the second team in 2006 when available.

He is a left handed batsman and right arm medium pace bowler who played in 3 'youth' test matches in 2006 for England under 19s against India under 19s.  He scored 266 runs, with a best of 113, at 44.33.  In 8 U 19 one day internationals he has scored 220 runs, with a best of 62, at 27.50.  He made his first class debut against Loughborough UCCE in May 2007, scoring 31 in his first knock at that level.

